(3, 'Abdomino-pelvic injuries - closed&nbsp;', 'No description', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Closed injuries are caused by compression force as in blow by fist\r\nor blunt instruments or crush injuries due to runover accidents and fall of a\r\nheavy object over the abdomen. No marks of wounds except superficial abrasions\r\nor contusion of skin and subcutaneous tissues. If the wound is present, it does\r\nnot extend into the peritoneal cavity and if there is no marks of external\r\ninjury, it is difficult to diagnose<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>', 'No description', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sudden hospitalization and appropriate care with regards to the\r\nintensity of the wound<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'No description', 'm', 30),
(4, 'Abdomino-pelvic injuries - open&nbsp;', 'No description', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Caused by sharp cutting or pointed instruments, like knife, razor,\r\nbullet or missile. Presence of lacerated, incised or penetrating wound is\r\ninvariably associated with its extension into the abdomen and so the peritoneal\r\ncavity is in direct communication with the environment. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">The intra-abdominal organs may be injured by the penetrating\r\nwounds which may be present in the anterior abdominal wall, side walls, back of\r\nthe abdomen, chest wall and perineum, gluteal and femoral triangle.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thorough exploration in the operation theatre<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Surgery if needed<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'No description', '', 0),
(5, 'Abnormal &nbsp;premenopausal bleeding', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Normal menstural bleeding lasts an average of 4 days (range 2 to\r\n7 days) with a mean blood loss of 40 ml. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Blood loss of over 80 ml per cycle is abnormal and frequently\r\nproduces anaemia<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excessive bleeding often with the passage of clots, may occur at\r\nregular menstrual intervals (menorrhagia) or irregular intervals (dysfunctional\r\nuterine bleeding)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When there are fewer than 21 days between the onset of bleeding\r\nepisodes, the cycles are likely to be anovular<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ovulation bleeding, a single episode of spotting between regular\r\nmenses, is quite common<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DUB is usually caused by overgrowth of endometrium due to\r\noestrogen stimulation without adequate progesterone to stabilize growth, this occurs\r\nin anovular cycles<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Anovulation associated with high oestrogen levels commonly occurs\r\nin teenagers, in women aged late 30s to late 40s and in extremely obese women\r\nor these with polycystic ovary syndrome<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'No description', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cervical smear needed for cytologic and culture studies<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Complete Blood count<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ESR<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Blood glucose to rule out DM (Diabetes may occasionaly\r\ninitially present with abnormal bleeding)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pregnancy test <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thyroid function test <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clotting time <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cevical biopsy and Endometrial curettage for identifying polyps,\r\nendometrial hyperplasia and submucous myomas<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Tests for ovulation in cyclic menorrhagia :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basal body temperature records<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Serum progesterone measured 1 week before the expected onset of\r\nmenses <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Analysis of an endometrial biopsy specimen for secretory activity\r\nshortly before the onset of menstruation<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Diagnosing CACX:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Multiple quadrant biopsies <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Colposcopy<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Endocervical curettage<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ultrasound evaluating endometrial thickness or to diagnose\r\nintrauterine or ectopic gestation or adnexal masses<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Endovaginal ultrasound with saline infusion sonohysterography may\r\nbe used to diagnose endometrial polyps or subserous myomas<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MRI can definitively diagnose submucous myomas and adenomyosis<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Hysteroscopy:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To visualize endometrial polyps, submucous myomas and exophytic\r\nendometrial cancers<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Done immediately before D and C<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Premenopausal patients\r\nwith abnormal uterine bleeding include those with submucous myomas, infections,\r\nearly abortion or pelvic neoplasms. DUB can usually be treated hormonally\r\nprogestins, which limit and stabilize endometrial growth, are generally\r\neffective<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D and C is usually not necessary in women under 40 years of age<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'No description', '', 0),
(6, 'Abnormalities of tooth structure&nbsp;', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Abnormal enamel :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enamel hypoplasia enamel is reduced in thickness or of deficient\r\nstructure, with pits and grooves or gross abnormalities<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enamel hypomineralisation enamel is of normal structure but not\r\nfully mineralised, with changes in colour and translucency<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Abnormal dentine : Dentinogenesis imperfecta - <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dentine consists of a reduced number of wide irregular tubules,\r\nwith areas of atubular dentine<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Loss of scalloping at Alveo dental junction (ADJ)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Teeth have opalescent bluish appearance<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Teeth wear rapidly as enamel is lost<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Result from disturbances during the period of tooth formation<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">May occur pre, peri or post-natally<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Amelogenesis imperfecta:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hypomineralised type normal matrix formation, abnormal\r\ncalcification, mainly autosomal dominant<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hypoplastic type abnormal matrix formation with normal\r\ncalcification of any matrix formed, mainly X-linked<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Abnormal cementum :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hypercementosis associated with over or underloading, Paget''s\r\ndisease<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hypocementosis associated with hypophosphatasia<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'No description', 'No description', 'No description', '', 0);
