(7, 'Abortion', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Spontaneous abortion is defined as a birth process terminating\r\nbefore the 20th completed week (139 days) of gestation<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It implies the expulsion of all or any part of the placenta or\r\nmembranes, with or without an identifiable foetus or with a live-born or\r\nstill-born infant weighing &lt; 500 gm.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incomplete abortion after the 10th gestational week<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;  Complete abortion is the expulsion of all of the products of\r\nconception before the 20th completed week of gestation, while in-complete\r\nabortion is the expulsion of some, but not all, of the products of conception\r\nin the same interval. Uterine perforation is manifested by signs of\r\nintraperitoneal bleeding, rupture of the bowel or bladder, or peritonitis<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Early abortion occurs before 12 weeks and late abortion at 12 to\r\n20 weeks<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Threatened abortion is bleeding of intrauterine origin occurring\r\nbefore the 20th completed weekwith or without uterine contractions, without\r\nexpulsion of the products of conception, and without dilatation of the cervix,\r\nrupture of the membranes, or expulsion of products<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inevitable abortion refers to the state in which bleeding of\r\nintrauterine origin occurs before the 20th completed week, with continuous and\r\nprogressive dilatation of the cervix and without expulsion of the products of\r\nconception with vaginal bleeding <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Missed abortion : </span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Here the embryo or foetus dies in\r\nutero before the 20th completed week of gestation, but the products of\r\nconception are retained in utero for 8 weeks or more.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Infected abortion is abortion associated with infection of the\r\ngenital organs and is contrasted to septic abortion, in which there is infected\r\nabortion with dissemination of infection through the maternal circulation<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Septic abortion presence of bacteria or their toxins or both in\r\nthe maternal organsand circulation<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Induced abortion the evacuation of products of conception in the\r\nuterus medically or surgically<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Subclinical (undiagnosed) spontaneous abortion : </span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Here the\r\npregnancy is resorbed or aborted before the pregnancy has been recognized.\r\nSpontaneous abortion generally occurs 1 to 3 weeks after the death of the\r\nembryo or foetus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Habitual abortion is defined as 3 consecutive pregnancy\r\nwastages before 20 weeks gestation with a foetus weighing less than 500 gm May\r\noccur bychance so karyotyping of the parents and maternal evaluation for\r\nabnormalities like incompetent cervix is advised<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prior to 37 weeks, regular uterine contractions with or without\r\npain or bleeding are abnormal, suggesting preterm labor<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A shortened effaced cervix prior to 32 weeks may indicate preterm\r\nlabor<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The most common cause of 1st trimester bleeding is abortion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arias-stella reaction is commonly seen<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Abdomen, hypogastrium and umbilical region colicky pain referred\r\nto low back and flanks&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">In spontaneous early abortion, haemorrhage into the decidua\r\nbasalis often occurs. Necrosis and inflammation appear in the region of\r\nimplantation<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">The pregnancy becomes partially or entirely detached and is, in\r\neffect, a foreign body in the uterus. Uterine contractions and dilatation of\r\nthe Cx result in expulsion of most or all of the products of conception<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">There are distinct patterns of spontaneous abortion. The amniotic\r\nsac and contents may be evacuated with the chorion and decidua; the embryo may\r\nbe expelled, with rupture of the amniotic sac and passage of the foetus alone;\r\nor the entire pregnancy and the decidua may be passed intact. In cases of\r\nmissed abortion, there may be partial organization of the blood clot\r\nsurrounding the conceptus. This results in the formation of a fleshy, nodular,\r\ndark red mass called a carneous mole, or blood (breus) mole.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Hydropic villous degeneration, a common finding in abortions\r\ncaused by ovular defects, may be due to an abnormal germ cell or accidental\r\ninjury to the developing embryo<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A fetus weighing 500 grams or more and gestational age of greater\r\nthan 20 weeks is called "potentially viable"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:green">System(s) affected</span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Reproductive<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:green">Genetics</span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Fetal chromosomal abnormalities Maternal to a much lesser extent<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:green">Age:</span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 15 years or less and then over 35 years <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incidence tends to decrease with age more than 15 years<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:green">Sex: </span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Female only<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Pregnancy tests :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Chorionic gonadotropin is produced by the syncytiotrophoblast.\r\nFalling or abnormally low plasma levels of beta-HCG are predictive of\r\nspontaneous abortion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Blood findings :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Anaemia if there is significant bleeding<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Increased WBC if infection (12,000 to 20,000/cmm)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Increased ESR. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Hormones :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With the possible exception of hypothyroidism, only the most\r\nextreme deficiencies in hormone secretion ever cause abortion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The greatest source of oestrogen in early pregnancy is\r\ntrophoblast; a small amount is secreted by the ovary.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A falling blood or urine oestrogen level may signify impending\r\nabortion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; During the 1st trimester, the principal source of progesterone is\r\nthe corpus luteum. Thereafter, the principal source is the chorioplacental system.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pregnanediol (the major catabolite of progesterone) and serum\r\nprogesterone drop precipitously in abortion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A small number of abortions appear to be due to a chronic luteal\r\ndefect and inadequate production of progesterone. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Vaginal smears :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The incidence of spontaneous abortion is related directly to the\r\npercentage of karyopyknotic cells in the vaginal smear obtained from the upper\r\nlateral vaginal wall.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The karyopyknotic index (K.I.) is the number of karyopyknotic\r\ncells per 100 exfoliated cells counted.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A normal K.I. is equal to or less than 10. The incidence of\r\nabortion in patients whose K.I. is more than 10 is approximately 20%.\r\nProgestogen therapy may benefit patients with a poor K.I. index who are\r\nthreatening to abort; however, it may not benefit patients who display the\r\nsigns and symptoms of abortion but who have a "good" K.I. index. When\r\noestrogen is inadequately opposed by progestogen, the cornification index\r\n(C.I.) increases as well as the K.I.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cultures for group B Streptococcus, gonorrhea and chlamydia<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Decreased hemoglobin<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Decreased hematocrit<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; HCG or its beta-subunit BHCG assayed in urine and plasma,\r\nqualitatively and quantitatively for presumptive detection of pregnancy <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tests for the early detection of pregnancy HCG in concentrated\r\nurine within two weeks of ovulation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Plasma assays of BHCG presumptive evidence of pregnancy at\r\nimplantation one week after ovulation and one week before the first missed\r\nperiod<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Human chorionic gonadotropin (HCG) -<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; HCG concentration in maternal plasma for assessment of fetal\r\nviability plasma HCG rises rapidly from the second through the ninth week of\r\ngestation. If it is stable or declining, fetal viability and normal pregnancy\r\ndoubtful<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ANA <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ACA<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; APA<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; LA<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TSH<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TORCH-8 <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">SPECIAL TESTS<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vaginal cytology karyopyknotic index over 20% progesterone\r\ndeficiency.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assesment of thyroid function<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Progesterone estimation (RIA)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Recurrent spontaneous miscarriage:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Karyotyping peripheral blood of both parents<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Karyotyping fetal products<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pelvic ultrasound to assess ovaries and uterus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tests for antiphospholipid antibodies twice, taken 6 weeks apart\r\nwith a third test taken if discordant results<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Laparoscopy:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp; &nbsp; Uterine perforation\r\nsuspected to determine the extent of laceration or bowel injury<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The need for laparotomy is primarily based upon these findings <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">IMAGING<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ultrasonogram :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ultrasonography is highly accurate in diagnosing impending\r\nspontaneous abortion and is being used increasingly, especially by the vaginal\r\nroute.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Impending abortion : The features of an impending abortion as\r\nvisualized on US include :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A poorly formed sac that is collapsed or that demonstrates poor\r\ngrowth over a period of 7 to 14 days.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A collapsed, crescent-shaped sac or an angular sac that is\r\nabnormally implanted close to the cervix may also be seen.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The echogenic trophoblastic rim is usually irregular in\r\nthickness, with areas in which no trophoblast is seen. However, poorly formed\r\nsacs may still develop normally<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A clot between the sac and internal os.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Absence of a foetal pole after the time at which it should be\r\nseen or a foetal pole without cardiac motion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ultrasound examination for fetal viability and to rule out\r\nectopic pregnancy<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ultrasound imaging can be sensitive enough to confirm an\r\nintrauterine pregnancy in the fourth or fifth gestational week<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">DIAGNOSTIC PROCEDURES<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identification of fetal heart sounds by Doppler\r\ninstrumentation at/or after the ninth week of gestation. Identification of\r\nfetal parts or gestational sac ultrasound<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Presumptive signs of pregnancy amenorrhea, increasing\r\nuterine size and correspondingly abdominal size, softening of the cervix,breast\r\nsoreness/swelling, presenceof HCG in urine or blood<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Products of conception within the material expelled from the\r\nuterus spontaneous abortion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Source of bleeding determined by sterile speculum examination.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cultures for group B Streptococcus, gonorrhea and chlamydia.\r\n<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Catheterized urine for urinalysis and culture.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A bimanual exam to assess uterine size and consistency or\r\ndilation of the cervix<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assessment for adnexal mass or tenderness<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; &nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Explore all cases of first trimester vaginal bleeding<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Serial quantitative BHCG analysis<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Threatened abortion:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bed rest and insert nothing per vagina. Severe bleeding more\r\nthan a heavy period hospitalization and close observation. Reassurance and\r\nmobilization gradually if USG confirms live fetus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bleeding and uterine cramping without cervical dilatation\r\ninternal os closed<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Therapy rest and observation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rule out ectopic or cervical lesions<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Inevitable or incomplete abortion: <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hemorrhage or rupture of membrane with cervical dilatation\r\ninternal os dilated<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Therapy evacuaton of the uterus by curettage<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evacuate the uterus promptly<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Typing and screening for requirements of transfusion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Suction D and C is effective for retained products when\r\ncompleteness of an abortion is doubtful.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.T. if bleeding is brisk or if the initial Hb% less than 10 gm%.\r\nGive 5% ringers lactate dextrose fluid IV with 10 units of oxytocin per 500 ml<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When completeness of abortion is in doubt, D &amp; C should\r\nalways be accomplished and tissue should be sent for histopathological\r\nexamination<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Do not do a vigorous "total curettage" because uterine\r\nsynecnias (Asherman''s syndrome) may result.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evacuate the uterus\r\npromptly<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Suction D &amp; C is\r\neffective<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.T. if bleeding is\r\nbrisk or if the initial Hb% less than 10 gm%. Give 5% ringers lactate dextrose\r\nfluid IV with 10 units of oxytocin per 500 ml<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When completeness of\r\nabortion is in doubt, D &amp; C should always be accomplished and tissue should\r\nbe sent for histopathological examination<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp; Do not do a vigorous\r\n"total curettage" because uterine synecnias (Asherman''s syndrome) may\r\nresult.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Incomplete abortion:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Some products of conception are expelled, but some remain in the\r\nuterine cavity Patulous os<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Therapy evacuation of uterus by curettage.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Complication profuse bleeding<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Missed abortion:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Death of the foetus without the onset of labor more than 4 weeks<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TherapyÃ¢â‚¬â€curettage.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Uterine growth stops, brown discharge, DIC occur.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Carneous mole (blood mole, fleshy moleÃ¢â‚¬â€clotted blood with\r\ncontained ovum less than 12 weeks)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The patient should be carefully reexamined 2 to 4 weeks following\r\nthe suspected diagnosis<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If there is evidence of a seriously reduced fibrinogen level,\r\ninfection, or anaemia, the uterus should be evacuated<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Early in gestation evacuation of the uterus is usually\r\naccomplished by suction curettage<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the 2nd trimester or later, the most common practice is to\r\ninduce labour using prostaglandin E suppositories<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Concentrated glucose or saline injection to induce labour in\r\nmissed abortion may be ineffectual and hazardous<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If bleeding or hypofibrinogenemia develops, I.V. B.T. by blood\r\nreplacement products may be required<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Septic abortion:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Infection of the conceptus and upper genital tract.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp; More commonlyÃ¢â‚¬â€mixed infection (peptostereptococcus and E. coli)\r\nendotoxins release<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TreatmentÃ¢â‚¬â€antibiotics and evacuation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ComplicationsÃ¢â‚¬â€peritonitis, endotoxic shock. Acute renal failure\r\nwith tubular necrosis (seen with Cl. welchii)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Always hospitalize the patient and start high dose antibiotic\r\ntherapy I.V. Use broadest spectrum drugs<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Give whole B.T and I.V. 5% Ringers lactate glucose with 10 units\r\nof oxytocin through a No. 18 needle. Determine urinary output.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Periodic estimation of C.V.P., cardiac output, blood volume and\r\nblood gases may be essential for successful management<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Abdominal hysterectomy should be considered when clostridia are\r\nthe responsible organism, when uterine perforation has occurred or when the\r\npatient responds poor after being in septic shock<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vena caval clipping and ovarian vein ligation may be indicated\r\nwhen repeated septic pulmonary embolization occurs<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D and C should be do, but hysterectomy may have to be carried out\r\n<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Habitual abortion:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cerclage (cervical stich) suspected cervical incompetence<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;Complete abortion:</span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When the products of conception are expelled en masse.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cervical os is closed.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Subsidence of abdominal pain and vaginal bleeding.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Anti-D gamma globulinÃ¢â‚¬â€im within 72 hr<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The patient should be observed for further bleeding<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clipping or ligation of the vena cava, internal iliac and ovarian\r\nveins<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;Successful management of\r\nabortion depends upon early diagnosis -<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Every patient should receive a general examination and a complete\r\nhistory should be obtained.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Late studies should include:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Culture and sensitivity of cervical mucus.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Blood typing and cross matching<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A complete hemogram (TLC/DLC, Hb%, ESR, Total RBC, PT, platelets\r\netc)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Endocrine deficiency should determined by appropriate tests.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Abortion has occurred after the 1st trimester, the patient\r\nshould be hospitalized. In all cases, give oxytocics e.g., oxytocin, 1ml/500 ml\r\nof 5% dextrose in lactated Ringer''s solution I.V. or 0.5 ml IM every 30 minutes\r\nfor 2 to 4 doses, to contract the uterus and limit blood loss and aid in the\r\nexpulsion of clots and tissues.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ERGOT preparations, which contract the Cervix as well as the\r\nuterus, should be given only if the diagnosis of complete abortion is certain.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Give antishock therapy, including blood replacement, to prevent\r\ncollapse after haemorrhage.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Place the patient at bed rest and give sedative to allay uterine\r\nirritability and limit bleeding.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coitus and douches are strictly contraindicated.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D &amp; C should be performed for possible retained tissue.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Start an oxytocin IV drip prior to surgery to avoid uterine\r\nperforation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">APPROPRIATE HEALTH CARE<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Psychological approach of early loss of pregnancy<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acknowledge and attempt to dispel grief<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Legitimize grief<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide comfort, empathy and on-going support<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reassure about the future (if less than 3 miscarriages risk of\r\nfurther miscarriage is not increased)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Counsel on how to fell friends and family<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Warn of anniversary phenomenon or sadness they may feel on birth\r\nof another''s baby<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Include partner<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">ACTIVITY<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Bed rest until resolution in milder cases<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ectopic pregnancy : </span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">It is the probable cause of menstrual abnormality, unilateral\r\npelvic pain, uterine bleeding, and a tender adnexal mass A potentially\r\nlife-threatening condition. Similar to threatened abortion and difficult to\r\ndifferentiate. Ultrasound helps to differentiate. Culdocentesis presence of\r\nfree peritoneal blood.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Membranous dysmenorrhoea : </span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">It is characterized by cramps, bleeding, and passage of\r\nendometrial casts. Decidua and villi are absent, amenorrhoea does not occur.\r\nHCG negative.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hyperoestrogenism in the nonpregnant woman causes abnormal\r\nuterine bleeding.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hydatidiform mole usually ends in abortion before the 5th\r\nmonth. Theca lutein cyst, when present, causes bilateral ovarian enlargement;\r\nthe uterus may be unusually large. Bloody discharge may contain hydropic villi\r\nUltrasound An intrauterine grape-like mass Human chorionic gonadotropin (HCG)\r\noften positive.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extruding pedunculated myoma.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cervical neoplasia (Polyps, carcinoma etc.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Non-obstetric conditions e.g. friable cervix, cervical\r\npolyps, neoplasias, or inflammatory conditions cause vaginal bleeding. There\r\nwillnot be any pain or cramping. Speculum examination is diagnostic.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `disease` (`disease_id`, `disease_name`, `keynotes`, `basics`, `lab`, `treatement`, `diagnosis`, `sex`, `age`) VALUES
(10, 'Abruptio placentae', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Premature detachment of the placenta from uterus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Placental abruption is a premature separation of a normally\r\nimplanted placenta.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Placental abruption classically presents as painful vaginal\r\nbleeding with a firm tender uterus.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp; &nbsp; An ultrasound should be\r\ndone prior to vaginal exam.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A pregnant woman in the third trimester who presents with painful\r\nvaginal bleeding, lower abdominal and back discomfort, and painful uterine\r\ncontractions<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Caused by the sudden decompression of the uterus in cases of\r\nrupture of membranes in patients with polyhydramnios or after delivery of the\r\nfirst of multiple fetuses<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The mother and the fetus may die of hemorrhage, and further\r\ncontractions may<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; worsen the\r\nabruption<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Abruption is also the most\r\ncommon cause of consumptive coagulopathy in<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; pregnancy;\r\ntherefore, transfusions should be given to those patients requiring it<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; with close follow-up\r\nof the coagulation status<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Premature separation of otherwise normally implanted placenta<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vaginal bleeding in the third trimester (more than one pad or\r\ntampon per hour)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Back pain<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Abdominal pain<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Uterine pain constant with or without contractions<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Uterine tenderness <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hypertonia<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Blood loss upto the level of shock<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Blood loss exceeding 30% before signs of shock or\r\nhypovolemia<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tachycardia <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Most common cause of hypofibrinogenemia is Abruptio placentae<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Commonest cause of acute renal failure in pregnancy is abruptio\r\nplacentae<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Commonest cause of consumptive coagulopathy in pregnancy is\r\nabruptio placentae<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The commonest haematological finding in placental abruption is\r\nhypofibrinogenaemia<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An interval of 10 years or more between births may cause in the\r\nsubsequent pregnancies increased incidence <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Thee grades and the third one has two types: Sher''s grade 1\r\nminimal or no bleeding, detected as retroplacental clot after delivery of\r\nviable fetus Sher''s grade 2 viable fetus with bleeding and tender irritable\r\nuterus. Sher''s grade 3 type A with dead fetus and no coagulopathy Sher''s grade\r\n3 type B with dead fetus and coagulopathy (about 30% of grade 3''s)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p