ottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fibrinogen levels climb to 350-550 mg/dl (3.5-5.5 g/L) in\r\nthird trimester and must fall to 100-150 mg/dl (1.0-1.5 g/L) before PTT will\r\nrise<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fibrin split or\r\ndegradation products are elevated in pregnancy so not very helpful to assess\r\ndisseminated intravascular coagulation (DIC)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Normocytic normochromic anemia with acute bleeding<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Elevated PT, PTT, fibrinogen levels below 100-150 mg/dl (1.0-1.5\r\ng/L), platelets 20,000-50,000 if DIC active<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Positive Kleihauer-Betke reaction if fetal-maternal\r\ntransfusion has occurred<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Positive antibody if RhoD isosensitization has occurred<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">SPECIAL TESTS<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kleihauer-Betke for fetal-maternal transfusion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bedside clot test with red top tube of maternal blood with\r\npoor or non-clotting blood after 7-10 minutes coagulopathy<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Test for fetal blood origin: </span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">mix\r\nvaginal blood with small amount tap water to cause hemolysis, centrifuge\r\nseveral minutes, mix pink hemoglobin containing supernatant with 1 cc 1% sodium\r\nhydroxide (NaOH) for each 5 cc supernatant, reading color in two minutes with\r\nfetal Hb staying pink and adult Hb turning yellow-brown<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Wright stain vaginal blood, observe for nucleated RBC''s\r\nusually of fetal origin<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lecithin/sphingomyelin (L/S) ratio if delay of delivery is\r\nconsidered and length of pregnancy is preterm<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">IMAGING<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Ultrasound show sonolucent retroplacental clot, rounded placenta\r\nmargin or thickened placenta. Not definitive (if with posterior placement or\r\nmild abruption)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Associated findings include :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Echogenicity of one placental lobe due to fresh bleeding.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Elevation of the chorioamniotic membrane from retroplacental\r\nblood.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clotted blood adjacent to the placenta<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">DIAGNOSTIC PROCEDURES<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">External uterine monitoring elevated baseline pressure and\r\nfrequent low amplitude contractions. Remember a good history and physical exam with\r\npast medical history, allergies, prior ultrasounds this pregnancy, and time of\r\nlast meal<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hospitalization until stable<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hemodynamic stabilization and delivery <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Delivery can be postponed while awaiting fetal lung maturity if\r\nthere is limited abruption and no fetal or maternal distress. Any evidence of\r\ndistress is an indication for immediate C-section<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">GENERAL MEASURES<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In general, severe abruption best managed by delivery of\r\nfetus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sher''s grade 1 usual labor protocol<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sher''s grade 2 varies with situation urgency<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sher''s grade 3 vaginal delivery preferable if mother stable<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In trauma monitor inpatient at least 4 hours for evidence of\r\nfetal insult, abruption, fetal-maternal transfusion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Early aggressive restoration of maternal physiology to\r\nprotect fetus and maternal organs from hypoperfusion or DIC<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Stabilize vitals, keep H.ct &gt;30, urine output &gt;30\r\ncc/hr<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bedrest with external fetal and labor monitoring, if fetus\r\nis viable<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Large bore 16-18 gauge IV crystalloid infusion, central line\r\nplacement only after coagulation status has been assessed<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Attend to the basic ABC''s with arterial blood gases (ABG) if\r\nacidosis suspected<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Follow hemoglobin/hematocrit (H/H) and coagulation status\r\nevery 1-2 hours<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Place intrauterine pressure catheter (IUC) since fetal risk\r\nclimbs with elevated pressure<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Amniotomy to prevent amniotic fluid embolism and to speed\r\ndelivery (debatable)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Positioning on left side to enhance venous return and\r\ncardiac output up to 30%<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Oxygen for all patients (oxygen consumption up 20% in\r\npregnancy and fetus especially hypoxia sensitive)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Trauma after observation or small abruption and preterm\r\nobserve in out patient to encourage reduction of risk factors<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; May need c/s after maternal stabilization if fetus viable\r\nand situation urgent<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">ACTIVITY<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Bedrest until status defined<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">DIET<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">NPO until status defined and cesarean section possibility ruled\r\nout<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">PATIENT EDUCATION<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">In preterm mild abruption not necessitating delivery, teach about\r\nrisks and causes<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Uterine rupture<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Placenta previa<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vasa previa<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Marked bloody show<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cervical causes (chlamydia or gonorrhea with bloody, friable\r\ncervix)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vaginal causes(chlamydia or gonorrhea with bloody, friable\r\ncervix)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Masses <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Other painful conditions like appendicitis or pyelonephritis<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Labor.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '', 0),
(11, 'Abscess, acute', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Localized collection of pus in a cavity formed by disintegration\r\nof tissues<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">An abscess is the end product of unresolved inflammation\r\nconsisting of a collection of pus surrounded by an inflammatory zone and a\r\nlining of granulation tissue. Pus is a fluid composed of living and dead\r\nbacteria, dead fixed cells and free cells representing the body''s phagocytic\r\nresponse and foreign material such as sutures, implants and splinters. It may\r\nbe superficial or deep and shows presence of pus within it<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">Acute abscess has all the classical signs of the inflammation,\r\nviz. swelling, pain (characteristically throbbing in nature), fever (high grade\r\nfever with rigors), redness, and impaired function of the affected part. The\r\npatient looks and feels ill<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'No description', 'No description', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Chronic abscess slight or absent inflammatory signs, hectic fever\r\nwith sweating, exhaustion, wasting and anaemia<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; "><b><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:maroon">&nbsp;COMPLICATIONS</span></b><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-left: 25.5pt; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -20.25pt; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Antibioma if antibiotics have sterilized the pus<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ã¢â‚¬Â¢&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expansion and further\r\ndestruc</span>', '', 0),
